# Milestone NN: Descriptive Name

## Goal

Describe the slice of test execution this milestone covers.
Typical examples: "smoke (elaboration + basic data flow + idle /
backpressure)"; "edge (boundary values, corner cases per
operation)"; "stress (long runs, saturation, target verification)";
"random (constraint-randomized, fixed-seed)"; "coverage (run
llvm-cov, record measurement)".

## Tasks

Each task names a concrete `#[test]` function DM3c will author.
At most 10 `- [ ]` rows per file
(`docs/plan-management.md` enforces the cap).

- [ ] test_name -- one-line purpose
  - pass criteria: `<specific, measurable>`
  - traces to: `<spec section / target row / decomposition op>`

- [ ] test_name_seed_42 -- one-line purpose (random milestones
  pin a seed in the test name)
  - pass criteria: `<specific, measurable>`
  - traces to: `<reference>`

## Notes

Special notes for this category:

- Smoke milestones MUST cover elaboration + basic data flow.
  Combinational designs may carry an explicit
  `RESOLVED: design has no flow-control surface, backpressure /
  idle entries do not apply` line in place of those tests.
- Stress milestones MUST exercise the targets in
  `docs/targets.md`.
- Random milestones MUST pin a seed in each test name
  (`<test>_seed_<N>`); failures must be reproducible from the
  seed alone.
- Coverage milestones run the command from `coverage.md`, then
  record the measured percentage in `test-plan.md`'s
  `## Coverage` section.

## Auto-decisions

Record non-trivial inferred choices, merged tests, or deferred
rows here.
